('Paul Raymond Smith', 'Paul Raymond', 'Smith', 'Experienced Hospitality Manager with a real passion for people', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/paul-raymond-smith-194b1673', 'paul-raymond-smith-194b1673', $${"about": "I’ve spent the last 20 years working in the hotel industry across three different continents. My experience ranges from Budget all the way up to Luxury Hotels. Although 20 years is a long time for some, it still feels the same as it did on day one and I still get the same buzz from interacting with guests and colleagues.\n \nMy journey first began as a F&B and Kitchen Attendant, from where I moved up into different roles, gaining experience across numerous departments along the way and eventually achieving my current role of General Manager at Grand Mercure Khao Lak Bangsak. \n \nI bring a guest-centric mindfulness that allows me to find new and interesting ways of engaging and satisfying guests. I am a solid and reliable operator who can handle day-to-day challenges calmly and effectively, and have had my fair share of crises to deal with over the years. I believe my time spent working within the day-to-day operations has given me a good grounding, which allows me to better understand the challenges of all teams and departments. In recent years, I have developed a good understanding of distribution, sales and marketing and feel confident leading all areas of a hotel team.\n \nI truly believe that inclusion, compassion and humility are the most effective ways to be successful within our industry, a bit of humor and fun around the hotel is also a must for me. I benefited massively from the time others put into my development and I try to pay this forward as often as possible. In my opinion, having a happy and engaged team always gets the best results.\n \nWhen I have time off, I love to spend it outdoors and have taken up a number of water sports since moving to Thailand. A perfect day off for me is time spent with loved ones on the beach. \n \nIf you ar